
                                            Parliament’s inquiry into Eskom continues on Wednesday, to shed light on alleged wrongdoing at the parastatal.
                                         CAPE TOWN - Parliament’s inquiry into Eskom  continues on Wednesday morning, with lawmakers expected to call a “critical witness” to shed light on alleged wrongdoing at the parastatal. The Portfolio Committee on Public Enterprises began with a presentation from UCT Professor Anton Eberhard on how state entities have been used to benefit a corrupt elite. It follows revelations in leaked emails of influence peddling by the Gupta family to score lucrative state contracts.   WATCH: MPs grill former Eskom boss Brian Dames 